./CHANGELOG.md:177:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw config status reports (frac-0046): `promptclaw/config.py` now exposes a frozen `ConfigStatusReport` plus typed helpers `enabled_agents`, `config_status_report`, `summarize_config`, and `load_or_default` so callers can inspect the project name, artifact root, control-plane mode/agent, default task type, agent count, sorted enabled/disabled agent name tuples, and validation issues in one diagnostic call. `enabled_agents` returns deterministic alphabetical names; `summarize_config` is JSON-safe and exposes lists rather than tuples; `load_or_default` returns the persisted config when `promptclaw.json` is present and otherwise returns `default_project_config(project_name)` without writing to disk. Existing `default_project_config`, `config_path`, `load_config`, `save_config`, and `validate_config` signatures and behavior are preserved. `tests/test_promptclaw_config_depth.py` pins enabled-agent ordering, default and invalid-config status reports, JSON-safe summary lists, the load-or-default branch, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_config.py` remains the regression anchor for existing load/validate behavior.
