./CHANGELOG.md:187:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw path layouts (frac-0041): `promptclaw/paths.py` now exposes a frozen `RunPathLayout` plus `ProjectPaths.run_layout()`, `ProjectPaths.ensure_run_layout()`, and `ProjectPaths.path_summary()` so project/run filesystem contracts can produce typed layouts, idempotently prepare run directories, and emit JSON-safe operator summaries. Existing project-level path attributes and `run_*` helper return values are preserved; `ArtifactManager.create_run_layout()` now iterates the canonical run layout while keeping the same on-disk `.promptclaw/runs/<run-id>/` structure. Empty run ids fail fast with `ValueError` before layout creation. `tests/test_promptclaw_paths_depth.py` pins helper compatibility, JSON-safe summaries, layout preparation through `ArtifactManager`, run-id rejection, and fractal depth >= 2; config, orchestrator, artifact, and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
./CHANGELOG.md:189:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw artifacts read path (frac-0040): `promptclaw/artifacts.py` now exposes `ArtifactManager.read_events()` which parses `events.jsonl` line by line and reconstructs the same `Event` dataclass shape that `append_event()` writes, returning `[]` when the log file does not yet exist. The four filename-taking write helpers (`write_prompt`, `write_output`, `write_handoff`, `write_summary`) now reject empty/whitespace-only filenames with `ValueError` before any I/O, matching the orchestrator's existing call-site contract while failing fast at the boundary. Existing public method signatures, on-disk filenames, JSONL serialization shape, and orchestrator call sites are preserved. `tests/test_promptclaw_artifacts_depth.py` pins the round-trip read, missing-log empty result, empty-filename rejection across the four filename helpers, normal-filename acceptance, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_orchestrator.py` and `tests/test_config.py` remain the regression anchors for end-to-end run behavior and config loading.
./CHANGELOG.md:287:- Added a steady-state SDP cap summary (T-032@c): `promptclaw.sdp_cost` now exposes `DailyCapCheck`, `CostCapSummary`, `read_csv`, `check_daily_caps`, `summarize_daily_cap`, `render_cap_summary`, and `write_cap_summary`, plus optional CLI flags `--summary-out`, `--daily-cap-usd`, and `--min-days`. The committed `sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cap-summary.md` links to `sdp/telemetry/cost-model.md`, checks seven active UTC days from `sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv` against the documented `$5.00` daily cap, and reports **FAIL** with seven breaches. Regression coverage in `tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py` pins exact-at-cap pass behavior, breach overage formatting, minimum-day failure behavior, CLI failure status on breach, and the committed summary artifact.
