./docs/architecture.md:211:Heavy long-lived artifacts now have an archive-root contract too. Runtime helpers prefer `CYPHERCLAW_ARCHIVE_ROOT` when set, otherwise they use `/mnt/archive/cypherclaw` on machines where the 10TB archive disk is mounted, then fall back to the older `/home/user/cypherclaw-data` layout or a project-local archive directory. That storage root now owns Litestream file replicas, archive-daemon outputs, rendered sample-event WAVs, and the porch/side camera capture rings, which keeps those high-growth paths off the NVMe root volume.
